211
00:10:12,166 --> 00:10:13,375
Enjoy!

212
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:18,833
[SAYA]
Hm?

213
00:10:18,916 --> 00:10:21,125
What is your opinion?
Do you approve?

214
00:10:21,208 --> 00:10:23,416
It's crazy, but I
actually like it!

215
00:10:23,500 --> 00:10:24,666
Wonderful!

216
00:10:24,750 --> 00:10:26,166
[SAYA]
The candy tastes like chocolate,

217
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:28,083
but also kind of
like grapes too,

218
00:10:28,166 --> 00:10:30,041
so it's sort of refreshing!

219
00:10:30,125 --> 00:10:32,125
And it's really good!

220
00:10:32,208 --> 00:10:35,708
A simple <i>dagashi</i> is allowed
to shine for a single moment,

221
00:10:35,791 --> 00:10:38,875
but then opens up a new path
for an unknowing traveler.

222
00:10:38,958 --> 00:10:41,750
To think that we might not
have achieved such a milestone

223
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:46,125
if it weren't for poo!
Yes, our beloved poo!

224
00:10:46,208 --> 00:10:47,625
Aw, man!

225
00:10:47,708 --> 00:10:48,958
[giggles]

226
00:10:49,041 --> 00:10:51,875
Because it's just us girls,
I want to be honest.

227
00:10:51,958 --> 00:10:55,208
It may sound silly, but I've
wanted to ask you something.

228
00:10:55,291 --> 00:10:56,958
Yeah, what?

229
00:10:57,041 --> 00:10:58,833
Okay, well.

230
00:11:01,041 --> 00:11:02,208
[HOTARU]
See the back?

231
00:11:02,291 --> 00:11:04,625
